bug.short_desc: [prov] Support aggregating of multiple bundles.txt files

long_desc.thetext:
For background, see discussions between Jim and myself and wiki documents ([1], [2], etc.).
I'm currently experimenting with a modified version of the test written for bug #212774 that splits bundles.txt into two files. Does anyone have any thoughts regarding how it is best to load from both files? In the long run I think we'll want to have n locations of small bundles.txt that we'll want to aggregate so should we have something like:
- main bundles.txt - directory location with small bundles.txts (we read all files in there) - user bundles.txt
?
I'll wait until later to set up bug blocks/depends for the other shared install goals.
[1] http://dev.eclipse.org/mhonarc/lists/equinox-dev/msg03383.html
[2] http://wiki.eclipse.org/Equinox_p2_Shared_Install_Plan

I'm having a hard time testing my experiments without a reliable test (see bug #212774).
In the meantime, I've got a question: Pascal and I talked about having fallbacks for startup in certain cases. An example is for starting only a system list of bundles if a user list causes issues. It's a bit undefined, I know, and may never happen, but it affects this bug in a way. My question is: should we aggregate the contents of the various bundles.txt files in advance of attempting to load them or try to load each one individually? I'm specifically thinking about SimpleConfiguratorImpl.applyConfiguration() here.
